99ad8fa8.description: This internship provides an opportunity to work on real-world product  development, involving all aspects of the software lifecycle — from system design  and development to deployment and maintenance.  Interns will collaborate in an agile environment, contribute to live projects, and  follow structured workflows using Git and GitHub for version control and  collaboration. The role encourages adaptability and cross-platform thinking to  deliver efficient, reliable, and maintainable software systems.  Key Responsibilities  Design, develop, and maintain modules as part of ongoing product development.  Write clean, efficient, and well-documented code.  Collaborate using Git and GitHub for version control and peer collaboration.  Contribute to product discussions, sprint reviews, and technical improvements.  Conduct testing, debugging, and optimization to ensure performance and  reliability.  Maintain consistent communication, documentation, and progress tracking  throughout the internship.  Adapt to evolving technical requirements and multi-platform environments. Key Responsibilities  Design, develop, and maintain modules as part of ongoing product  development.  Write clean, efficient, and well-documented code.  Collaborate using Git and GitHub for version control and peer collaboration.  Contribute to product discussions, sprint reviews, and technical  improvements.  Conduct testing, debugging, and optimization to ensure performance and  reliability.  Maintain consistent communication, documentation, and progress tracking  throughout the internship.  Adapt to evolving technical requirements and multi-platform environments.  Preferred Additional Skills  Exposure to cross-platform development environments or frameworks.  Awareness of testing, deployment, and optimization processes.  Familiarity with UI/UX principles, documentation practices, or agile workflows.  Strong debugging and problem-solving mindset.  Eligibility  Open to 2nd and 3rd year B.E. / B.Tech students in Computer Science,  Information Technology, or related branches.  Must be available full-time for the 3-month internship duration.  Should have a genuine interest in end-to-end product development and  software engineering.  What You’ll Gain  Experience in complete product development cycles and collaborative  software engineering.  Exposure to professional development workflows and tools.  Practical understanding of version control, testing, and deployment.  Mentorship and guidance throughout the internship.  Selection Process  1. Resume Shortlisting  Applications will be screened based on academic performance, technical skills,  and relevant project experience. Candidates with GitHub activity or prior  development exposure will be given preference.  2. Technical HR Interview  Shortlisted candidates will attend a virtual technical interview focusing on  programming fundamentals, problem-solving ability, and understanding of  development workflows. 3. General HR Interview  The final round will assess communication skills, adaptability, and alignment  with the organization’s values and work culture.  Final selections will be based on overall performance and suitability for the  internship role.
